My poor Kyon just can’t seem to catch a break 😔 Over the last couple of months, I’ve noticed him get very stiff in his rear end after running. Last week at flyball practice was the worst I had seen it, and he looked like he was super uncomfortable. Luckily, we were able to get in to see an orthopedic specialist last night, and he believes that Kyon has “lumbosacral stenosis”… basically a slipped disc in his lower back. 😓 The positive news is that it is very treatable - there are some conservative and surgical options to consider, but no final decision can be made until he gets a CT scan in January… Day to day, we don’t see any pain, and he is begrudgingly benched (or should I say couched?) from sports until we get a definitive diagnosis. Please sending healing vibes his way as we tackle this obstacle 🙏 And if anyone has experience with this diagnosis I would love to chat ❤️‍🩹 #kyon #kyonstrong #fighthardplayharder #thistooshallpass #keepfighting #belgianmalinois #malinois #malinoislovers #belgianshepherd #maligator #k9 #dogtraining #happydog #cute #fetch #rawfed #doggo #bestfriend #dog #offleash #puppygram #dogoftheday #dogsofinstagram #bayarea #sanjose #puppy #workingdog #instadog #dogmom #doglover

Kyon went in for another exam with an ortho and neuro specialist yesterday. After some more poking, prodding and pulling, they believe that most of Kyon’s pain is coming from an iliopsoas injury… although there *may* be some pain in his LS area, the majority of his discomfort is visible when engaging his psoas. 😖 Instead of moving straight into advanced imagery and more aggressive options, we have decided to rest for a month with targeted, controlled exercise and then a recheck to see where we are, and if we need to consider other options. ❤️‍🩹 As hard as it is going to be to have Kyon sidelined for some time, I’m incredibly thankful he shows zero pain in day to day activities, and that he is still his happy go lucky self. We have a long road ahead of us, but we all know Kyon is a fighter, and I am hoping that he will come back from this set back stronger than ever. 💪 #kyon #kyonstrong #fighthardplayharder #dogsport #iwillbeback  #belgianmalinois #malinois #malinoislovers #belgianshepherd #maligator #k9 #dogtraining #happydog #cute #rawfed #doggo #bestfriend #dog #offleash #puppygram #dogoftheday #dogsofinstagram #bayarea #sanjose #puppy #workingdog #instadog #dogmom #doglover

Kyon went back in for a recheck with his orthopedic specialist yesterday… we had gone to practice Saturday, and I tried flat, restrained recalls for him for the first time since December. As much as I was thrilled to see how he’d improved, it was crushing to see that he still wasn’t back to his pre-injury range of motion. 😔 We spoke with his Dr (and a few colleagues who have experienced similar injuries) and have concluded we made too big of a jump into explosive movement and need to take a step back and break things down a bit further. We reviewed neurological and other orthopedic possibilities, but the illiopsoas injury still fits Kyon’s symptoms the best. 🤕 So we are back to the drawing board and breaking his rehab into smaller pieces to get his body comfortable with a variety of movement types again. His specialist team still has full confidence that he will return to sports, it will just take a bit longer than we initially anticipated. And if that is what my boy needs to be his happiest, healthiest self, than we will keep working and rehabbing hard. 💪 And I can only hope that one day he can join me back in the lanes to play and scream the song of his people in my face… I really do miss that sound… ❤️ #kyon #kyonstrong #fighthardplayharder #roadtorecovery #sportdog #makingacomeback #belgianmalinois #malinois #malinoislovers #belgianshepherd #maligator #k9 #dogtraining #happydog #cute #rawfed #doglife #bestfriend #dog #offleash #puppygram #dogoftheday #dogsofinstagram #bayarea #sanjose #puppy #workingdog #dogstagram #dogmom #doglover
